Summaries for MAT2A Gene

Entrez Gene Summary for MAT2A Gene

  • The protein encoded by this gene catalyzes the production of S-adenosylmethionine (AdoMet) from methionine and ATP. AdoMet is the key methyl donor in cellular processes. [provided by RefSeq, Jun 2011]

GeneCards Summary for MAT2A Gene

MAT2A (Methionine Adenosyltransferase 2A) is a Protein Coding gene. Diseases associated with MAT2A include acute maxillary sinusitis and glycine n-methyltransferase deficiency. Among its related pathways are Carbon metabolism and Sulfur amino acid metabolism. GO annotations related to this gene include methionine adenosyltransferase activity. An important paralog of this gene is MAT1A.

UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot for MAT2A Gene

  • METK2_HUMAN,P31153

  • Catalyzes the formation of S-adenosylmethionine from methionine and ATP.
